syncthing evaluation

What is syncthing?
	Peer to Peer connection.
	We can EITHER
		1) just use the library of the current syncthing and build on top of it
		2) actually customize syncthing to have OSF as the only (and by default) peer. 
How does the client work?
	the default one is a webpage that runs on localhost.	
	there are also multi-platform clients written by seperate developers.
Can we easily connect to the OSF api using syncthing?
	
Event API?
	long-polling api that alerts you when files are changing on local machine
REST API?
	control overall operation of syncthing and querying status of syncthing.
Technologies used?
	golang core
	multi-platform clients written in golang and python
Security?
	
